---
import SectionTag from '../SectionTag.astro';
import FadeIn from '../FadeIn.astro';
---

<div>
  <SectionTag label="About" theme="work" />

  <FadeIn>
    <!-- Intro card: photo + name/role -->
    <div class="about-intro">
      <img
        src="/images/headshot.jpg"
        alt="Tommaso Babucci"
        class="about-photo"
      />
      <div class="about-intro-text">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'Krona One', sans-serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 400; color: #1C1917; line-height: 1.25; margin-bottom: 8px;">
          Tommaso Babucci
        </h2>
        <p style="font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; color: #B53B2E; letter-spacing: 0.03em;">
          AI Strategy &amp; Development &mdash; Ernst &amp; Young
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bio accordion (exclusive — only one open at a time) -->
    <div class="bio-accordion type-body-work" style="color: #57534E;">
      <!-- Now (open by default) -->
      <div class="bio-accordion-item">
        <button class="bio-accordion-trigger" aria-expanded="true">
          <span class="bio-accordion-label">Now</span>
          <span class="bio-accordion-icon" style="transform: rotate(45deg);">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="bio-accordion-body is-open">
          <p>
            Day to day, I bring together a cross-functional team of strategists, developers, designers
            and marketers creating and scaling new AI narratives and offerings globally. The work ranges
            from product development and tech partnerships to AI training for a 120,000-person organization
            and speaking at industry events around the world. The mission: helping EY transform into an
            AI-native organization.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Journey -->
      <div class="bio-accordion-item">
        <button class="bio-accordion-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="bio-accordion-label">Journey</span>
          <span class="bio-accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="bio-accordion-body">
          <p>
            The journey started on the other side of the table, as one of EY's first GenAI developers
            building custom AI products for clients in consumer and automotive. Before that, a machine
            learning startup optimizing Amazon advertising. Once you learn to sell the car, you want to
            learn how to build it. That led to <strong style="color: #1C1917;">USC Marshall</strong>
            for a Master's in Business Analytics, where I still serve on the Board of Advisors.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Origin -->
      <div class="bio-accordion-item">
        <button class="bio-accordion-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="bio-accordion-label">Origin</span>
          <span class="bio-accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="bio-accordion-body">
          <p>
            But before the code, the consulting, the keynotes, there was a magazine. Moved from Milan
            to <strong style="color: #1C1917;">Duke University</strong> and ended up leading a 120-person
            creative team. That's where the instinct for storytelling and building new things rooted and grew.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Too much information -->
      <div class="bio-accordion-item">
        <button class="bio-accordion-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="bio-accordion-label">Too much information</span>
          <span class="bio-accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="bio-accordion-body">
          <p>
            Avid if inconsistent reader. Curiosity rabbit holes have taught me about tea ceremonies,
            regenerative agriculture, and Brazilian jiu-jitsu. My wife calls me her &ldquo;personal ChatGPT&rdquo;.
            I love to cook. Have worked and lived in Italy, the UK, and the US.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </FadeIn>
</div>

<!-- Bio accordion: exclusive behavior (only one open at a time) -->
<script is:inline>
  (function() {
    document.querySelectorAll('.bio-accordion-trigger').forEach(function(trigger) {
      trigger.addEventListener('click', function() {
        var acc = this.closest('.bio-accordion');
        var body = this.nextElementSibling;
        var wasOpen = body.classList.contains('is-open');

        // Close all sections
        acc.querySelectorAll('.bio-accordion-body').forEach(function(b) {
          b.classList.remove('is-open');
        });
        acc.querySelectorAll('.bio-accordion-icon').forEach(function(icon) {
          icon.style.transform = 'rotate(0deg)';
        });
        acc.querySelectorAll('.bio-accordion-trigger').forEach(function(t) {
          t.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
        });

        // Toggle this one (open if it wasn't already)
        if (!wasOpen) {
          body.classList.add('is-open');
          this.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
          this.querySelector('.bio-accordion-icon').style.transform = 'rotate(45deg)';
        }
      });
    });
  })();
</script>
